msgid "How to use this service from the command line"
msgstr "How to use this service from the command line"

msgid "You can use various command-line tools such as curl, httpie, and wget to use this service. Taking the most popular one, curl, as an example:"
msgstr "You can use various command-line tools such as curl, httpie, and wget to use this service. Taking the most popular one, curl, as an example:"

msgid "Query current IP:"
msgstr "Query current IP:"

msgid "Query information for your own IP:"
msgstr "Query information for your own IP:"

msgid "Or display all information in JSON format:"
msgstr "Or display all information in JSON format:"

msgid "Query information for a specific IP:"
msgstr "Query information for a specific IP:"

msgid "How to force the display of my IPv4 or IPv6 address?"
msgstr "How to force the display of my IPv4 or IPv6 address?"

msgid "You can use <code>curl -4</code> or <code>curl -6</code> to view only your IPv4 or IPv6 address respectively."
msgstr "You can use <code>curl -4</code> or <code>curl -6</code> to view only your IPv4 or IPv6 address respectively."

msgid "How to get a JSON format response?"
msgstr "How to get a JSON format response?"

msgid "You can send a request to the <code>/json</code> endpoint, or send a request with an <code>application/json</code> header."
msgstr "You can send a request to the <code>/json</code> endpoint, or send a request with an <code>application/json</code> header."

msgid "Can I automate calls to your service via programs?"
msgstr "Can I automate calls to your service via programs?"

msgid "Certainly, as long as the rate limit is respected. Under normal conditions, the rate limit is 30 RPM (Requests Per Minute); under high load, we will increase the restriction to 10-5 RPM."
msgstr "Certainly, as long as the rate limit is respected. Under normal conditions, the rate limit is 30 RPM (Requests Per Minute); under high load, we will increase the restriction to 10-5 RPM."

msgid "Our API is only suitable for manual calls or small-scale projects. If your website uses our API to query visitor IPs, please ensure you use a message queue to send requests to avoid blocking. If your project has high traffic or is latency-sensitive, please use our open-source offline database: <a href=\"https://github.com/NetworkCats/Merged-IP-Data\">Merged IP Database</a>, which is the same database used by this project."
msgstr "Our API is only suitable for manual calls or small-scale projects. If your website uses our API to query visitor IPs, please ensure you use a message queue to send requests to avoid blocking. If your project has high traffic or is latency-sensitive, please use our open-source offline database: <a href=\"https://github.com/NetworkCats/Merged-IP-Data\">Merged IP Database</a>, which is the same database used by this project."

msgid "Where does the IP data come from?"
msgstr "Where does the IP data come from?"

msgid "IP geographic data primarily comes from the free databases of MaxMind and DB-IP; AS data comes from IPinfo's free database; and IP proxy data comes from my own <a href=\"https://github.com/NetworkCats/OpenProxyDB\">OpenProxyDB</a> database."
msgstr "IP geographic data primarily comes from the free databases of MaxMind and DB-IP; AS data comes from IPinfo's free database; and IP proxy data comes from my own <a href=\"https://github.com/NetworkCats/OpenProxyDB\">OpenProxyDB</a> database."

msgid "Data Attributions:"
msgstr "Data Attributions:"

msgid "Can I run my own service?"
msgstr "Can I run my own service?"

msgid "Yes, the source code and database for this project are both open-source and hosted on GitHub:"
msgstr "Yes, the source code and database for this project are both open-source and hosted on GitHub:"

msgid "How is this website different from other IP lookup sites?"
msgstr "How is this website different from other IP lookup sites?"

msgid "The biggest difference is that our database includes proxy-related information, and the proxy intelligence we provide is highly accurate. We have privately compared it with commercial proxy detection databases like IPinfo; our database's precision is fully comparable to commercial ones, and it is even more accurate in detecting residential proxies."
msgstr "The biggest difference is that our database includes proxy-related information, and the proxy intelligence we provide is highly accurate. We have privately compared it with commercial proxy detection databases like IPinfo; our database's precision is fully comparable to commercial ones, and it is even more accurate in detecting residential proxies."

msgid "Secondly, our geographic coverage for IPv6 is more comprehensive because we merge multiple databases to provide more complete data."
msgstr "Secondly, our geographic coverage for IPv6 is more comprehensive because we merge multiple databases to provide more complete data."

msgid "Our UX is also better than any IP lookup site on the market. The site runs without any JavaScript, and we only load a minimal amount of external resources (fonts, icons), making the initial load speed extremely fast."
msgstr "Our UX is also better than any IP lookup site on the market. The site runs without any JavaScript, and we only load a minimal amount of external resources (fonts, icons), making the initial load speed extremely fast."

msgid "Is this service stable?"
msgstr "Is this service stable?"

msgid "The business logic of this service is written entirely in Rust, offering excellent performance that ensures the site remains operational even under L7 DDoS attacks. The site runs on a VPS with 2 cores and 2 GB of RAM, which is already overkill for this setup -- unless we encounter a massive L7 DDoS attack, though we have Cloudflare in front of us."
msgstr "The business logic of this service is written entirely in Rust, offering excellent performance that ensures the site remains operational even under L7 DDoS attacks. The site runs on a VPS with 2 cores and 2 GB of RAM, which is already overkill for this setup -- unless we encounter a massive L7 DDoS attack, though we have Cloudflare in front of us."

msgid "Running this website only costs me $18.00 per month. Because the cost is so low, I will not stop operations due to hardware costs in the foreseeable future, nor will I add any advertisements."
msgstr "Running this website only costs me $18.00 per month. Because the cost is so low, I will not stop operations due to hardware costs in the foreseeable future, nor will I add any advertisements."

msgid "Rest assured, this service will definitely not \"Rug Pull.\""
msgstr "Rest assured, this service will definitely not \"Rug Pull.\""

